A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 20, 2025, as Alpha Day at the Capitol; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Inc., the first intercollegiate Greek-letter fraternity
3 established for African American men, was founded at Cornell University in Ithaca, New
4 York, on December 4, 1906, by Henry Arthur Callis, Charles Henry Chapman, Eugene
5 Kinckle Jones, George Biddle Kelley, Nathaniel Allison Murray, Robert Harold Ogle, and
6 Vertner Woodson Tandy; known as the "Jewels," these men recognized the need for a strong
7 bond of brotherhood among African descendants in this country; and
8 WHEREAS, for 118 years, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Inc., has been a beacon of light to
9 the community by staying true to its aims of manly deeds, scholarship, and love for all
10 mankind; and
11 WHEREAS, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Inc., has a membership of more than 70,000
12 college-educated men inducted into over 700 college and alumni chapters in the United
13 States, Europe, Asia, and the Caribbean; and
14 WHEREAS, this esteemed fraternity continues to live out its mission of developing leaders,
15 promoting brotherhood and academic excellence, and providing service and advocacy for our
