16 communities by contributing more than $2.3 million in educational scholarships and
17 volunteering 850,000 community service hours; and
18 WHEREAS, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Inc., counts many renowned Georgians as
19 members, including Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., Ambassador Andrew Young, Mayor
20 Maynard H. Jackson, Senator Raphael Warnock, Congressman David Scott, W.E.B. Dubois,
21 Dr. Louis Sullivan, Actor Omari Hardwick, John Hope, and newly elected State Senator
22 RaShaun Kemp; and
23 WHEREAS, the 18th Annual "Alpha Day at the Capitol" convenes under the leadership of
24 Georgia District Director James Ford II, Assistant District Director Mark Nooks Jr., and
25 Political Action Committee Chairman Aaron Johnson, representing 42 chapters across the
26 state.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
28 urge all citizens to recognize and applaud the contributions of Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity,
29 Inc., and the Georgia District in their commitment to making our communities a better place
30 as well as recognize February 20, 2025, as Alpha Day at the Capitol.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
32 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Alpha Phi Alpha
33 Fraternity, Inc., the public, and the press.
